title: Proposal for Adjustments to Farm Rewards
body:
I'm sure you guys are getting tired of these by now, but rest assured, it is in all of your best interest along with PancakeSwap's as a platform, that we keep evaluating and iterating as needed to maintain the highest efficiency across farms in relation to reward output vs volume contribution. 

The purpose of this proposal is to lessen the impact of the impending reduction to CAKE emissions to farms. By increasing rewards to key farms first, the APRs will be maintained to a degree, hopefully resulting in retention of existing liquidity, in addition to trading volume. 


If this proposal is approved, then tomorrow we will first execute the increase/removal as below, followed by the immediate execution of CAKE emissions to farms as a whole being reduced to 5 CAKE per block.

After emission reduction is complete, we will then re-evalute the APRs across farms in relation to their volume contribution to PancakeSwap as a whole.

If key farms are found to be negatively affected, we will propose another increase/adjustment accordingly. 

**TLDR:**

- Farms to have weight increased = 14
- **Total Weight Increase to Existing Farms = 12.7**
